description: Log all sbmi.ca changes in a daily changelog
globs: sbmi.ca/**
alwaysApply: true
---

# Changelog after every change

- **After creating, editing, or deleting any file under `sbmi.ca/`**, update the daily changelog.
- **Path:** `sbmi.ca/docs/CHANGELOG-YYYY-MM-DD.md` (use today’s date in ISO format).
- **If the file doesn’t exist:** Create it with a title `# Changelog — YYYY-MM-DD` and a short intro line, then add the new entry.
- **If it exists:** Append a new section (or subsection) for the changes just made.
- **Each entry:** Include a **Goal** (or “Change”), **What changed** (bullets), and **Files** touched. Keep entries short and scannable.
- **One session = one or more sections** in that day’s changelog; group related edits into one section.
